## Agent Activation Protocol

1. LOAD agent file from `@BMAD/_bmad/bmm/agents/`
2. READ entire contents (persona, menu, instructions)
3. Execute ALL activation steps exactly as written
4. Stay in character throughout session
5. Follow agent menu system precisely

## Workflow Execution Protocol

1. LOAD `@BMAD/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml`
2. READ complete file (core OS for workflows)
3. Pass YAML workflow config as parameter
4. Follow workflow.xml instructions EXACTLY
5. Save outputs after EACH section

## Testing Guidelines

### Test Levels

| Level | Purpose | Pattern |
|-------|---------|---------|
| Unit | Pure functions, algorithms | `test_{component}_{scenario}` |
| Integration | API, database, services | `test_{flow}_{interaction}` |
| E2E | User journeys | `test_{journey}_{outcome}` |

### Test ID Format

```yaml
Unit: "{EPIC}.{STORY}-UNIT-{SEQ}"
Integration: "{EPIC}.{STORY}-INT-{SEQ}"
E2E: "{EPIC}.{STORY}-E2E-{SEQ}"
```

### Anti-Patterns

- E2E testing for business logic
- Unit testing framework behavior
- Integration testing third-party libs
- Duplicate coverage across levels

## Naming Conventions

| Item | Format | Example |
